      #normlize data
      #first np.log1p() normlize : function ln(x + 1) , decode needs np.expm1():exp(value) - 1
      #then  Standard normlize : (x - mean) / std     , decode needs mean and std: value * std + mean
      TEST_RECORDS_NUM = 240
      def standard_normlize(df,test_records_num):
          from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler
          y_scaler = StandardScaler()
          X_scaler = StandardScaler()
          y_df = df.pop('in')
          X_df = df
          y_real_for_test = y_df[len(y_df)-test_records_num:len(y_df)]
          y_real_for_train = y_df[0:len(y_df)-test_records_num]
          X_scaled = X_scaler.fit_transform(X_df)
          y_real_for_train_scaled = y_scaler.fit_transform(np.array(y_real_for_train).reshape(-1,1))
          X_scaled_df = pd.DataFrame(X_scaled)
          y_real_for_train_scaled = pd.DataFrame(y_real_for_train_scaled)
          y_real_for_test_scaled = pd.DataFrame(y_scaler.transform(np.array(y_real_for_test).reshape(-1,1)))
          y_scaled_df = pd.concat((y_real_for_train_scaled,y_real_for_test_scaled))
          all_scaled_data_df = pd.DataFrame(np.hstack((np.array(y_scaled_df).reshape(-1,1),np.array(X_scaled_df))),columns=('in','out','rain1','rain2','rain3'))
          return all_scaled_data_df,X_scaler,y_scaler
      def log1p_normalize(df):
          return np.log1p(df)

      def norm2ori(norm,std_scaler):
          norm_log1p = norm * std_scaler.var_**0.5 + std_scaler.mean_
          ori = np.expm1(norm_log1p)
          return ori

      class OffsetPeriodOptimizer(object):
          def __init__(self,estimater,method,src=None,data=None):
              self.estimater = estimater
              self.method = method
              self.data = data
              self.results = None
              
          def objective_func(self,x):
              train_x, test_x, train_y, test_y = util.get_train_test_split(None,self.data,int(np.round(x[0])),int(np.round(x[1])),with_rain=True)
              #print(train_x.shape,train_y.shape)
              self.estimater.fit(train_x,train_y)
              y_hat = self.estimater.predict(test_x)
              return mean_squared_error(y_hat,test_y)
          
          def optimization(self,lower_bounds=np.array([36,5],dtype=np.float32),upper_bounds=np.array([60,25],dtype=np.float32)):
              from robo.fmin import random_search,bayesian_optimization,entropy_search
              results = None
              if(self.method == 'bayesian_optimization'):
                  self.results = bayesian_optimization(self.objective_func, lower=lower_bounds,
                                                  upper=upper_bounds, num_iterations=200,
                                                  acquisition_func='ei')
              elif(self.method == 'random_search'):
                  self.results = random_search(self.objective_func, lower=lower_bounds,
                                          upper=upper_bounds, num_iterations=200)
              else:
                  pass

      print(X.shape,y.shape,type(X))
      def add_formerN_points_mean_std(X,period,N=[5,12,24]):
          X_df = pd.DataFrame(X)
          for i in N:
              X_df[f'{i} points mean in'] = X_df[[i for i in range(period,period + i)]].mean(axis=1)
          for i in N:
              X_df[f'{i} points std in'] = X_df[[i for i in range(period,period + i)]].std(axis=1)
          return X_df
      X_df = add_formerN_points_mean_std(X,20,[i for i in range(2,21,2)] + 
                                              [i for i in range(5,21,5)] +
                                              [i for i in range(7,21,7)] +
                                              [i for i in range(11,21,11)])
